headlines.description: Playing without its top quarterback and running back, Auburn used tandems at each position to set a season scoring high and beat Virginia 43-24 in the Chick-fil-A Bowl on Saturday night.

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Northwestern Wildcats

notes.headline: MEINEKE CAR CARE BOWL OF TEXAS

headlines.description: — Zach Clement threw four touchdown passes, Northwestern State held Texas A&M-Commerce scoreless in the second half and the Demons posted a 41-14 win over the Lions on Saturday to remain undefeated in Southland Conference play.

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Utah Utes

headlines.description: John White plowed into the end zone from 8 yards out to give Utah a 30-27 overtime victory against Georgia Tech in the Hyundai Sun Bowl on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: White carries Utah to Sun Bowl win in OT

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Terry Hawthorne returned an interception 39 yards for Illinois' first touchdown late in the third quarter and the Illini snapped a six-game losing streak by beating UCLA 20-14 in the Fight Hunger Bowl.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illini win Fight Hunger Bowl, stop slide

headlines.description: Isaiah Pead ran for 149 yards and a touchdown, and Ralph David Abernathy IV's 90-yard kickoff return early in the fourth quarter put Cincinnati ahead to stay as the Bearcats edged Vanderbilt 31-24 on Saturday in the Liberty Bowl.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincy fights off Vandy in Liberty Bowl
